1
00:00:01,180 --> 00:00:08,440
So, the task is to build a voltage inverter rated 800 volts, 2 amps.

2
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:22,500
The load will be 300-watt lamps, 4 of them connected in series, and bundled in parallel as 3 strings — 3 bundles of 4 lamps in parallel.

3
00:00:23,060 --> 00:00:29,460
4 lamps per bundle to distribute the 800 volts as 200 volts per lamp.

4
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:50,000
So, we have a ferrite step-up transformer, we have a half-bridge inverter, this is the control board, the mains rectifier, and we'll be watching the consumption.

5
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,380
So, we start it up.

6
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:59,320
We start the logic.

7
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:02,860
Off we go.

8
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:06,440
That's how this thing lights up.

9
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:19,140
Our consumption is 7.5 amps at 220 volts, AC ammeter.

10
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,580
Shutting it off, or the strip will burn out.
